OL,6,FHowever in many respects what the
OL,7,FCulture Secretary said was a
OL,8,Fstatement of the obvious ` of simple
OL,9,Fcommon sense and political expediency.
OL,11,FPut simply, there are no votes in
OL,12,Fswitching off Freeview and every
OL,13,Fpossibility, indeed probability, of
OL,14,Flosing them.
OL,16,FImagine if a previous generation of
OL,17,Fpoliticians had promised they would
OL,18,Fswitch off 405-line TV in 1970 or
OL,19,Fanalogue terrestrial in 2000.
