OL,6,FMy hunch is that this will only
OL,7,Fhappen when the transmitters fail or
OL,8,Fonce it is very obvious that hardly
OL,9,Fanyone is listening.
OL,11,FIf the day should eventually come
OL,12,Fwhen Freeview faces closure, you can
OL,13,Fexpect several years' notice and a
OL,14,Fhuge campaign to provide information
OL,15,Fand help for the vulnerable.
OL,17,FThe bigger risk to Freeview is that
OL,18,Fwithout more HD it simply will become
OL,19,Fa legacy service.
